node.text: Last Saturday we had an 11th birthday party for Tuna and my goodness did he LOVE schlomping on his dog-friendly cake! He LOVED IT! Just listen! #schlomp

clips_music_attribution_info.should_mute_audio_reason: Instagram music isn't available in your region.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} on August 03, 2021 tagging @marky2dix. May be a cartoon.

node.text: My heart is aching that he’s in the US and we’re in the UK, and it’s only day 2! Oh how I wish he could charter his own plane and meet us over here. This brilliant #tunainterpretations is how I envision it happening thanks to @marky2dix. #tunartuesdays

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} on August 02, 2021 tagging @wyliemae_me. May be an image of dog and indoor.

node.text: Ian, Grace, and I made it safely to the UK and we’re so stoked to be back with our family here. In other news, we are missing this #toodlebrain terribly, but I’m happy to report that he is having the time of his life back in our other homeland with his auntie @wyliemae_me, his brother Fisch, and sissy-friend, Mandy!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} on August 02, 2021 tagging @wyliemae_me. May be an image of dog and indoor.
Photo shared by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} on August 02, 2021 tagging @wyliemae_me. May be an image of dog and outdoors.
Photo by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} in Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport. May be an image of 1 person and airplane.

node.text:
When we created the 2020 Essential Edition calendar last year, we had no idea that we would be flying to London on the 1st of August, so this August Pilot photo is just perfect for today! Thank you to everyone in the airline industry for keeping us all safe as we travel! We are so grateful!

We cannot wait to see our family and friends in the UK after being away from them for such a long time. Sadly, Tuna will not be joining us this trip because airline’s have changed their policy with pets flying in the cabin to the UK, but he will be in the excellent care of his aunt Wendy and his brother Fisch while we are away! 

I won’t be posting as much while we are in the UK, so as to be present with our family, but when I do, I may be posting some archive photos, which I will indicate. 

Lastly, thank you for all of the birthday wishes yesterday. I will be posting more about his birthday in a couple of days! We love you all! Xx

node.text: If you’ve been following Tuna for any length of time you know that he HATES flies. #ad And since we live in the south we get lots of them, as well as ants, roaches and almost every other insect you can think of! We initially started using @zevoinsect because of our bug issue, but what we really LOVE about it is that it’s safe to use around dogs and children when used as directed. Zevo is made with friendly ingredients you can feel good about, and it effectively targets and shuts down biological pathways found in bugs, not people or pets, without using harsh chemicals, which we also love! Visit the link in Tuna’s bio under Zevo or head to his stories to see more and get more information! #WaySmarterThanBugs

node.text: Did you know that I’m American (although I’m an Anglophile) and Tuna’s dad is British? So do you think that Tuna has an American or British accent? Head to his stories to hear (and see) for yourself and then comment below. 🇺🇸🇬🇧

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} in Trafalgar Square London with @martinjamesbushell.

node.text: It was #sharkweek a couple weeks ago, and next week we head to the UK where this sculpture hopefully still remains. Firstly, how did I miss this #tunainterpretations masterpiece because I would have DEFINITELY posted about it during #sharkweek, and secondly, I really hope this is in public because I will March over to Trafalgar Square to see it! Please let me know, @martinjamesbushell, and thank you so much for this incredible creation!

node.text: We are leaving in one week from today to visit our family across the pond. Unfortunately Tuna isn’t able to come with us this time, which breaks my heart, but he’ll be in the excellent care of his auntie Wendy and in the company of his beloved brother, Fisch. For this week only I put @cameo back up, so if you want a personalised video from him for someone you love, now is the time :) If you miss this window, they’ll be available again at the end of August. Link in his bio!

node.text: #ad Tuna loved the Original Series of Turner & Hooch on @disneyplus so much that he wanted to review it by reenacting it. As you can see, the new reboot is wildly entertaining, action-packed, hilarious, and family-friendly! Not to mention it’s adorable, thanks to slobbery Hooch. To stream the Original #TurnerAndHoochSeries on #DisneyPlus starring @shuapeck as Scott Turner, visit the link in Tuna’s bio or go to Tuna’s Stories and swipe up!

node.text: This sweet little angel face baby head got his remaining stitches removed today, so he wanted to model his face to show off. I seriously cannot reiterate how relieved and thankful I am that his markings were all benign! A MASSIVE THANK YOU, again, to Dr. Schick and her amazing team at Atlanta Veterinary Specialists. They are phenomenal and took SUCH great care of my baby. I couldn’t be happier with them and their services! 👏🙌

Did you know that we were given the opportunity to license and manufacture the Colin dolls for a limited time, exclusive to Tunameltsmyheart. For those who signed up for the Colin pre-sale details about a month ago, we will be sending out an email and posting more about that here in the coming weeks! If you haven’t signed up to be the first to get on the pre-sale list, go to the link in the bio to sign up for that under COLIN PRE-SALE SIGN UP! Stay Tuna’d.
